        "title": "feat(desktop): add Tauri model setup app",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Add the Tauri desktop app shell, runtime preparation/smoke scripts, native gateway sidecar launcher, and desktop packaging ignores for generated artifacts.\n- Add desktop model setup UI/controllers and gateway model probe support with guarded credential handling and redacted probe responses.\n- Wire desktop runtime/update/notification settings into the Control UI and add release-surface checks for CSP, runtime preparation, sidecar Node version, and bundled plugin bootstrap updates.\n\n## Verification\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/config/config-misc.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/models.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-native-bridge.test.ts ui/src/ui/controllers/desktop-model-setup.test.ts ui/src/ui/views/desktop-model-setup.test.ts ui/src/ui/storage.node.test.ts ui/src/ui/views/config.browser.test.ts ui/src/ui/views/login-gate.test.ts ui/src/ui/app.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-render.assistant-avatar.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-lifecycle.node.test.ts`\n- `pnpm build:plugin-sdk:dts`\n- `corepack pnpm desktop:smoke-runtime`\n- `cargo fmt --check && cargo check` in `apps/desktop/src-tauri`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode commit --commit HEAD`\n- `node openclaw.mjs --version`\n\n## Real behavior proof\nBehavior addressed: desktop users get a native Tauri app that can start/reuse a gateway sidecar, guide first-run model setup, expose desktop runtime/update/notification settings, and preserve existing config/agents while saving setup.\nReal environment tested: local macOS OpenClaw source checkout with targeted Vitest files, plugin SDK DTS build, desktop runtime smoke, Cargo check, and autoreview.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/config/config-misc.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/models.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-native-bridge.test.ts ui/src/ui/controllers/desktop-model-setup.test.ts ui/src/ui/views/desktop-model-setup.test.ts ui/src/ui/storage.node.test.ts ui/src/ui/views/config.browser.test.ts ui/src/ui/views/login-gate.test.ts ui/src/ui/app.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-render.assistant-avatar.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-lifecycle.node.test.ts`; `pnpm build:plugin-sdk:dts`; `corepack pnpm desktop:smoke-runtime`; `cargo fmt --check && cargo check`; `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode commit --commit HEAD`; `node openclaw.mjs --version`.\nEvidence after fix:\n```text\n$ node openclaw.mjs --version\nOpenClaw 2026.5.28 (5ff1cb9)\n$ corepack pnpm desktop:smoke-runtime\n[desktop:smoke-runtime] packaged OpenClaw entrypoint absent; dev fallback is expected for this smoke\n[desktop:smoke-runtime] ok\n$ cargo fmt --check && cargo check\nFinished `dev` profile [unoptimized + debuginfo] target(s) in 3.24s\n$ .agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode commit --commit HEAD\nautoreview clean: no accepted/actionable findings reported\n```\nObserved result after fix: desktop setup completion exits the setup gate, existing fallback-port gateways are reused, optional Lobster bootstrap failures no longer block gateway startup, and model probe credential handling avoids the reviewed redaction/exfiltration cases.\nWhat was not tested: full signed/notarized desktop bundle install/update flow and live provider credentials were not tested.\n",
